# MEMORY.md — agent entry point

This vault is a second brain with a strict trust model. If you are an agent
reading this: do not crawl the tree. Use the `second-brain` MCP tools or the
scripts under `70-scripts/search/`.

## Retrieval order (always)

1. `search_decisions` — accepted decisions beat everything else
2. `search_curated` — human-reviewed synthesis
3. `read_context_pack` — prebuilt task bundles in `50-context-packs/active/`
4. `search_agent_memory` — machine memory (unreviewed unless marked)
5. `search_sources` — converted documents (`trust_level: source-derived`)
6. Originals in `10-originals/` only when conversion is ambiguous — via a human

## Trust rules

- `review_status: unreviewed` means *not fact* — cite it as source-derived.
- Prefer `status: active` + `confidence: high` notes; skip superseded notes.
- Write observations to `40-agent-memory/` via the memory tools; never edit
  `30-curated/` or `10-originals/`.

